            @* Error handling note *@
            <section class="slide-up-delay-5 bg-slate-100 dark:bg-dgb-900/50 border border-slate-200 dark:border-dgb-800 rounded-2xl p-5">
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Error handling is identical across languages</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed m-0">
                    Every failure raises <InlineCode>DigiPayError</InlineCode> with the HTTP status preserved — branch on the number, not the message.
                    <code class="inline-block ml-1 text-[0.6875rem]">400</code> = validation,
                    <code class="inline-block text-[0.6875rem]">401</code> = bad token,
                    <code class="inline-block text-[0.6875rem]">404</code> = not found or not yours,
                    <code class="inline-block text-[0.6875rem]">429</code> = sandbox rate-limit,
                    <code class="inline-block text-[0.6875rem]">≥ 500</code> = server-side (retryable),
                    <code class="inline-block text-[0.6875rem]">0</code> = network / TLS / timeout.
                </p>
